3. RESULTS AND DISCUSSION
Interactive multimedia is applied in teaching Informatics subjects in class VII, adjusted to learning objectives in order to attract students' interest. In this case, students will be actively involved in learning activities. In order to produce valid and practical learning media, researchers must carry out validity assessments by media experts and material experts, as well as practicality tests through the use of questionnaires with Likert scales filled out by students.
